  "tips": [
    "Beautiful waterfall, although its flow varies a lot from year to year depending on the rain and snow that falls during the winter. Nearby there is a refuge for shepherds who work with their cattle in the summer months. Thus, almost with all probability you will be able to see herds of cows, horses and sheep of native breeds of the Pyrenees. In summer there is a little train that brings people closer to the waterfall for a short walk.",
    "It is a good end point for routes through the Ripera valley. Accessible with children.",
    "The Sabocos lake has a small cabin. Very photogenic! It has a small open shelter with 8 seats, although as seen in the photograph it already has owners (livestock). https://www.pyrenees-refuges.com/fr/affiche.php?numenr=1530"
  ],
